    <h3 class="font-weight-bold text-center text-info">
HELP PROTECT THE POLLINATORS
</h3>
<hr class="my-4">

    <p class="text-muted">
      Almost a <mark>third of the food we eat every day</mark> relies on pollinators, mostly bees,
      but also birds, butterflies, bats, beetles, moths, and flies. Bees and other pollinators
      are <mark>vital</mark> to stable and plentiful food supplies, a healthy environment, and a strong economy.

      <p class="text-muted">But populations of New York State honeybees and other pollinators are <mark>crashing at an alarming
      rate.</mark> The causes include the use of harmful pesticides and fungicides, the spread of viral
      pathogens and parasitic mites in beehives, loss of habitat, and the effects of climate change.
      If we don’t act right now to address this collapse, <mark>it will soon be too late.</mark>

      <p class="text-muted"><b>Beautify NY</b> is a conservation project that aims to help the endangered
      pollinators by creating beautiful wildflower gardens throughout the New York State Park System.</p>

      <h4 class="text-center">Want to help?
      <%= link_to 'Volunteer Now!', new_volunteer_path %>
      </h4>
