</h3>
<hr class="my-4">
        <p><ul class="list-group">
            <li class="list-group-item">» Over 200,000 animal species serve as pollinators.</li>
  <li class="list-group-item">» Of the 1,400 crop plants grown, nearly 75% require pollination</li>
      <li class="list-group-item">» Products produced in the U.S. due to pollination are worth $20 Billion</li>
  <li class="list-group-item">» Flowers bloom during the day and night, depending on which pollinator
    they need to attract. </li>
    <li class="list-group-item">» Many pollinators evolved with the plants they pollinate,
  and each developed special characteristics to make
  pollination more efficient. </li>
  <li class="list-group-item">» Flowers attract pollinators by color and scent. Some even emit UV light
    (the last to fade at dusk), prolonging pollination.</li>
    <li class="list-group-item">» A well-designed backyard can offer pollinators more living space, food and safety from predators. </li>

</ul>
